	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />A simple memory map would fit nicely in the first few lessons.  Something along the lines of:
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">CPU space &#40;directly accessible&#41;:<br />$0000 - $07FF&nbsp; 2KiB&nbsp; Built-in RAM &#40;freely read/write&#41;<br />$2000 - $2007&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Video registers &#40;special functions&#41;<br />$4000 - $401F&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Sound and Gamepad registers &#40;special functions&#41;<br />$6000 - $7FFF&nbsp; 8KiB&nbsp; Optional on-cartridge RAM &#40;freely read/write&#41;<br />$8000 - $FFFF 32KiB&nbsp; Program ROM &#91;PRG-ROM&#93; &#40;read-only&#41;<br /><br />PPU space &#40;accessible through $2006 and $2007&#41;:<br />$0000 - $1FFF&nbsp; 8KiB&nbsp; Pattern tables &#40;ROM or RAM, depending on cartridge type&#41;<br />$2000 - $27FF&nbsp; 2KiB&nbsp; Name and Attribute tables &#40;internal RAM&#41;<br />$3F00 - $3F1F&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Palettes &#40;internal RAM&#41;<br /><br />Sprite space &#40;accessible through $2003, $2004, and $4014&#41;:<br />$00 - $FF&nbsp; 256B&nbsp; Sprite data<br /></div>
<br />along with an explanation that all code is stored in the PRG-ROM, variables and RAM tables have to be manually initialized, Name tables need to be set up, and so on.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
